  "body": "Deploying a contract with forge create is not very intuitive (to me). Consider this contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: Unlicense\r\npragma solidity 0.8.10;\r\n\r\ncontract HelloWorld {\r\n    string private greeting;\r\n    uint public version = 0;\r\n\r\n    constructor (string memory _greeting) {\r\n        greeting = _greeting;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function greet() public view returns(string memory) {\r\n        return greeting;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function updateGreeting(string memory _greeting) public {\r\n        version += 1;\r\n        greeting = _greeting;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy first thought was to do `forge create -h`. From here I read that I must include the \"artifact\". I could not find any information on what \"artifacts\" are. I ended up figuring out that if you type the name of the contract (in this case \"HelloWorld\"), it would work.\r\n\r\nAfter I added the rpc-url and my private-key, I'm now getting a new error:\r\n\r\n`Error: 0:  Invalid Data`.\r\n\r\nI'm really not sure how to use `forge create` at this point. I can't find any tutorials or docs.\r\n",
